  <div class="explanation-container">
    <h3>Your employer don't pay your bonuses?</h3>
    <p>
       According to the Federal Labor Law, all workers are entitled to the following bonus:
       <ul>
        <li>Christmas bonus: the christmas bonus should beof at least fifteen days of your salary
        and should be payed before december 20 each year.</li>
        <li>Vacation bonus: should be at least 25% of your salary for each day of vacations.</li>
        <li>Employee profit sharing: The company should divide 10% of its profits between the workers
        according to their salary and worked days, this should be payed between march and april of the
        following year.</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <h3>What can you do?</h3>
    <p>
      The law protects you, so there are several resources you got at your disposal to defend your
      rights.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li> You can make a complaint to the <a href="https://www.gob.mx/stps">ministry of labour</a>, wich is in charge of overseeing the compliance
      of the correct bonus payment.
      </li>
      <li>The federal office for the defense of the worker, will provide you with legal advice
      you can contact them <a href="https://www.gob.mx/profedet">here.</a>
      </li>
      <li>Your local conciliation and arbitration board can help you mediate with your employer
      to arrive to a friendly solution.</li>
      <li>If everything else fails you can sue your former employer and be provided with a free defense attorney.</li>
    </ul>

    <br>

    <p>
      If you are not sure if your bous payment is correct you can use our <a href="calculations/new">calculator </a>
      that will give you the right amount.
    </p>
    <p>
      Also you can consult our <a href="forums/Unpaid%20Bonus">forum </a>and ask our community of law professionals
      or see if someone has had the same question as you.
    </p>
